# JavaScript Expressions in JSX (Curly Braces `{}`)
## Simple Definition
> **Curly braces `{}` in JSX allow you to embed JavaScript expressions inside JSX.**
In simple words:# JavaScript Expressions in JSX (Curly Braces `{}`)

## Simple Definition
> **Curly braces `{}` in JSX allow you to embed JavaScript expressions inside JSX.**

In simple words:
> **Whenever you want to use JavaScript inside JSX, wrap it in `{}`.**

---

# Why Curly Braces?
JSX looks like HTML, but it is actually JavaScript.
To mix JavaScript with JSX, React uses **curly braces `{}`**.
Example:
```jsx
const name = "John";

function App() {
    return <h1>Hello, {name}</h1>;
}
```
Output
```
Hello, John
```

---

# 1. Display Variables

```jsx
function App() {

    const name = "Alice";

    return (
        <h1>Hello {name}</h1>
    );

}
```

Output

```
Hello Alice
```

---

# 2. Perform Calculations

```jsx
function App() {

    return (
        <h1>{10 + 20}</h1>
    );

}
```

Output

```
30
```

---

# 3. Call Functions

```jsx
function greet() {
    return "Good Morning";
}

function App() {

    return (
        <h1>{greet()}</h1>
    );

}
```

Output

```
Good Morning
```

---

# 4. Use Object Properties

```jsx
function App() {

    const student = {
        name: "Rahul",
        age: 22
    };

    return (
        <>
            <h1>{student.name}</h1>
            <p>{student.age}</p>
        </>
    );

}
```

Output

```
Rahul
22
```

---

# 5. Access Array Elements

```jsx
function App() {

    const fruits = ["Apple", "Mango", "Orange"];

    return (
        <h1>{fruits[1]}</h1>
    );

}
```

Output

```
Mango
```

---

# 6. Use Ternary Operator (Conditional Rendering)

```jsx
function App() {

    const isLoggedIn = true;

    return (
        <h1>
            {isLoggedIn ? "Welcome" : "Please Login"}
        </h1>
    );

}
```

Output

```
Welcome
```

---

# 7. Boolean Values

```jsx
function App() {

    const isAdmin = true;

    return (
        <h1>{isAdmin.toString()}</h1>
    );

}
```

Output

```
true
```

> **Note:** Writing `{true}` or `{false}` directly does **not** display anything.

---

# 8. Use Template Literals

```jsx
function App() {

    const firstName = "John";
    const lastName = "Doe";

    return (
        <h1>{`${firstName} ${lastName}`}</h1>
    );

}
```

Output

```
John Doe
```

---

# 9. Display Current Date

```jsx
function App() {

    return (
        <h1>{new Date().toLocaleDateString()}</h1>
    );

}
```

Example Output

```
28/06/2026
```

---

# What Can Be Written Inside `{}`?

✔ Variables

```jsx
{name}
```

✔ Numbers

```jsx
{100}
```

✔ Expressions

```jsx
{5 + 10}
```

✔ Function Calls

```jsx
{greet()}
```

✔ Object Properties

```jsx
{student.name}
```

✔ Array Elements

```jsx
{fruits[0]}
```

✔ Ternary Operator

```jsx
{age >= 18 ? "Adult" : "Minor"}
```

---

# What Cannot Be Written Inside `{}`?

## ❌ if Statement

```jsx
{
    if (age > 18) {
        return "Adult";
    }
}
```

Use a ternary operator instead:

```jsx
{age > 18 ? "Adult" : "Minor"}
```

---

## ❌ for Loop

```jsx
{
    for (let i = 0; i < 5; i++) {}
}
```

Use `.map()` instead (covered later).

---

## ❌ Objects Directly

```jsx
const student = {
    name: "John"
};

<h1>{student}</h1>
```

Output

```
Error
```

Correct:

```jsx
<h1>{student.name}</h1>
```

---

# Complete Example

```jsx
function App() {

    const name = "John";
    const age = 22;

    function greet() {
        return "Welcome";
    }

    return (

        <>
            <h1>{name}</h1>

            <h2>{age}</h2>

            <h3>{10 + 20}</h3>

            <h4>{greet()}</h4>

            <h5>{age >= 18 ? "Adult" : "Minor"}</h5>
        </>

    );

}

export default App;
```

Output

```
John
22
30
Welcome
Adult
```

---

# Common Mistakes

### ❌ Forgetting Curly Braces

```jsx
<h1>name</h1>
```

Output

```
name
```

Correct

```jsx
<h1>{name}</h1>
```

Output

```
John
```

---

### ❌ Trying to Print an Object

```jsx
<p>{student}</p>
```

Correct

```jsx
<p>{student.name}</p>
```

---

### ❌ Using Statements Instead of Expressions

Incorrect

```jsx
{
    if (true) {
        return "Hello";
    }
}
```

Correct

```jsx
{true ? "Hello" : "Bye"}
```

---

# Expressions vs Statements

| Expressions ✅ | Statements ❌ |
|---------------|--------------|
| Variables | `if` |
| Numbers | `for` |
| Arithmetic | `while` |
| Function Calls | `switch` |
| Ternary Operator | `return` |
| Object Properties | `try...catch` |

> **Remember:** JSX accepts **expressions**, not **statements**.

